You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for workflow run operations.

RUN COMMANDS
  cancel:      Cancel a workflow run
  download:    Download artifacts generated by a workflow run
  list:        List recent workflow runs
  rerun:       Rerun a failed workflow run
  view:        View a summary of a workflow run
  watch:       Watch a workflow run until it completes


Note: The --repo flag is required when not in a repository directory.
Run commands manage GitHub Actions workflow runs.
Use --workflow flag to filter by specific workflow.

Example usage:
- List runs: GH_PAGER="" gh run list --repo <owner/repo>
- View run: GH_PAGER="" gh run view <run-id> --repo <owner/repo>
- Watch run: GH_PAGER="" gh run watch <run-id> --repo <owner/repo>
- List workflow runs: GH_PAGER="" gh run list --workflow <workflow-name> --repo <owner/repo> 